review:
Latest New Design Not User Friendly The new design is not intuitive to users.
It also doesn’t carry all the different categories of offers that are in the Straits Times, and these used to be in the old design of the app. I searched the entire newly designed app and can’t find the followings, which were obvious to users in the old design: 

1st: Deepavali Specials - the items listed under “Deepavali Draw” in the new design are NOT the same as those advertised in the Straits Times. Previously, they were the same and there was a clear and obvious designed category “Deepavali Specials” that I could click on to get the full list of items on offer.

2nd: 3-day Weekend Offers: This is not listed at all today in the new design. In the old design of the app, it was uploaded every Friday, to sync with the newspaper advertisement. Plus, users only needed to click “3-day Weekend Offers” to see all items on offer in this category in the old design.

3rd: Brands Offers: The old design was so easy and intuitive to use - just a click on the freebies from the different brands, users would see the various items of that specific brand to buy. Now, users only see the freebie & statement like “Free pan with $60 purchase”. Click it, users only see the free pan! Now, what users should see is what are the items to choose from to make up $60 to enjoy the free pan.

review:
Insincere and ridiculous business I’ve made a purchase or 36 packets of milo through the app. In the first week, i was told that they only have 12 in the warehouse and asked if i wanted to wait for more stocks before they deliver. I waited for about 1.5 weeks. By the second week, i called to check on the status and they claim that they have no more stocks left. They did not even kept the 12 packets of milo. What is outrageous is that their app still shows that they have the same kind of milo in stock. They refuse to change it for me and claimed it was out of stock. 

What is ridiculous is that their online warehouse operates on a different system then the retail stores. They ask me to call up each and every fairprice outlet to ask if they have the milo. They were not sincere in their apology and made me do their dirty work when it is their poor unprofessional mistake. I mean how hard is it to obtain 36 packets of milo?? 

I ordered from redmart the next day and they delivered promptly. It is the exact same brand of milo. 

Extremely disappointed at this whole delivery service. I wouldn’t even give one star if i have the choice.

BUT, the confirmation I received indicated the payment was done by card #1. This is one confused app. I checked the statement on card #2, noticed there is an unposted transaction on card #2 as well.

I called FairPrice customer service line, the agent claims there is only 1 transaction. I called the card issuer to block the transaction, the agent says nothing can be done from their side. 

I have been told I need to wait until transaction is posted and dispute. It is NOT my fault the payment screen doesn’t work as expected now I have to use my time to track the status and call back for the disputes. This is TERRIBLE customer experience! Utterly disappointed.

review:
Legit complaints from a frequent shopper I really hope NTUC succeeds in its foray into the digital space so hear me out here. 

1. Bad UX

- i can search when I’m not signed in, and when I want to add to my cart I have to sign in which is fair. But when I do, the stuff that I saw that was available is suddenly unavailable. For example, Pampers Premium Care.

- search results are not sorted according to type or relevance! Which is the bare minimum of an e-commerce app. For example, when I search for rice noodles, the first five results are rice noodles or noodles then a trickle of irrelevant products then rice noodles appearing then irrelevant products then rice noodles etc. Why??

- some search results are not relevant! when I search for “rice noodles” I am shown tomato paste, olive oil, canola oil, virgin coconut oil, mustard dressing etc. Why???

- after search results are displayed I have to scroll upwards manually to view starting from top to bottom. Why doesn’t it display from the top results?

- can you please place all the unavailable items towards the bottom of the search results instead of weaving them intermittently within the available items?

2. Bad fulfilment

The delivery service is really superb. On time, and within the same day of ordering even. However, I refrain from ordering fresh items like chicken or vegetables after a couple times bad experience where I was allocated stale chicken and very old vegetables. To be fair, Sheng Siong and RedMart both do poorly on this category. So should NTUC treat this gap as a major opportunity to outshine your competitors?

3. Bad inventory management

About 50% of the time, my confirmed orders are updated to exclude a couple of items that are not available.

100% of the time, many items that I want to buy aren’t available. I’m hard pressed to fill my cart of items worth $79 because so many items are unavailable!
